The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																		The Calcutta Municipal Corporation (CMC) on Tuesday finalised a deal with a private party to buy a three-bigha plot in Garden Reachs Gandhi Maidan area to set up a three-million-gallon booster water pumping station. A CMC official said the land will be handed over to the Calcutta Metropolitan Water and Sanitation Authority for the construction of the station. The project will cost around Rs. 10.5 crore. 																																																								he CMC will also construct 800 small residential quarters for the displaced workers of a Garden Reach jute mill.																																																		A gang of six armed dacoits raided and looted two houses in the Barasat police station area, on the northern fringes, early on Tuesday, police said. They decamped with cash and ornaments worth Rs 4 lakh. No arrests were made.																																																		Police on Tuesday conducted massive raids on various pockets of Howrah town and arrested 10 persons for selling fireworks without valid licences. A senior police officer said the daylong raids were carried out in areas like Balitikuri, Dasnagar and Icchapore. A large amount of fireworks was confiscated. 
